<br>
Arrington filled Elmpe glass with mead.  Elmpe continues, &quot;My hope is to reach a level of skill to be an asset to you fine people on future journeys whenever I can join you.&quot;  <br>
<br>
He looks up at the wall filled with portraits of past Heroes of the guild.  &quot;I am getting close to that level of expertise.&quot;  Elmpe smiles, &quot;I will return to this Hall and announce to you all when I have achieved my goal.&quot;<br>
<br>
Elmpe stands and waves good journey as he strides out into the dark night.<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uarrington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arrington</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.whisperingscythe.org/images/ws3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild member</span><br>  Posts: 368<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(8/2/02 10:34:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.gol.com/users/slowhand/image/wel_pen.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elmpe's Hope</span><hr size=1> Arrington stares out the window of the guild house, seeing only oblivion.  His heavy shoulders seem unable to allow his arms to hold his small hands above his waist.  Mournfully his voice cracks a little as he begins to speak.  &quot;Is this a see you later?  Or just goodbye?  In the past the monthly dues of around 12 bucks have taken my friends away.&quot;  Kicking a stray log into the fire he adds, &quot;Of course the evil King Verdant wants his due.&quot;  <br>
<br>
With a slightly happier stance he begins talking again.  &quot;I do not see our friend Giligan very often.  However, it makes the times I do see him even happier.  Same goes for Querkus and Hikanur.&quot;   <br>
<br>
With a movement of his hand and the loss of a bat's ability to fly he begins to float.  The gnome Runs out the door to the guild house.  Standing on the platform in front he screams, &quot;Don't make me do it.  I will do it! !&quot;  He jumps and softly floats to the ground.  <br>
<br>
A small summer storm appears as if summoned by a wish or a spell.  Arrington uses this opportunity to hide the feeling that seem to flow from his eyes.  <br>
<br>
/ooc Hopefully you will still be able to join us only less frequently.  When football season starts I will be missing a lot of EQ time myself.  I have tickets for 7 games to see ECU play, all on Saturday.  This will mean no playing on Saturday and little playing on Friday and Sunday, my biggest 3 days of playing.  However, after Thanks Giving I will return to playing more and maybe start getting levels again.  <br>
<br>
However, real life is much more important than a game.  If you need to go then I wish you well.  Just remember, you will be missed.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uelmpe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elmpe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild Member</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(8/2/02 11:52:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elmpe's Hope</span><hr size=1> Elmpe looks skyward on a dark star filled night.  He wonders how his guild mates are faring?  He knows he will see them again and that thought makes him smile.  &quot;When I am stronger Jaggedpine will be visited&quot; he vows.<br>
<br>
Elmpe shifts his gaze to his diary.  &quot;If only I had more time I could help my friends more often&quot; he thinks to himself.  He begins to write a tale of adventure and loyalty that does not end, but just moves at a slower but still powerful pace.  &quot;Sort of like the river that flows in Surefall glade&quot; he sighs.  <br>
<br>
With that Elmpe drifts off to sleep awaiting the next adventure that will gain him the experience he needs to assist his mates in the Whispering Scythe.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
