<br>
Elmpe knows he still has much to learn, but he is anticipating the day when he can again fight along side his guildmates.  &quot;Soon&quot; he whispers with determination and hope.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uhikanur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hikanur</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.whisperingscythe.org/images/ws3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild Officer</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(8/19/02 3:16:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elmpe's Hope</span><hr size=1> Elmpe,  I would suggest you go fight in Dreadlands and Sol B now.  You will do much better there than in the overthere now. Stay here or Sol B or both( for some change) untill level 50. Both of these zones are very good exp. and good loot till you get to 50 or so. Watch for trains in Sol B though. hehe <p>Hikanur a level 53 warrior <BR>
of the Whispering Scythe!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/uarrington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arrington</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.whisperingscythe.org/images/ws3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Whispering Scythe Guild member</span><br>  Posts: 385<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(8/20/02 7:14:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fscythe72844frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.gol.com/users/slowhand/image/wel_pen.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elmpe's Hope</span><hr size=1> I have one better on the moon.  I have been doing VERY well in Tenebrous Mountains with Quelar.  With the new ports on the moon including one to Twilight Sea we are able to get there quick.  Also Katta Castellum is right beside the zone so we have access to merchants and a bank.    Maybe we can get some almost raid level people bound in Katta Castellum and work on getting them up.  <br>
<br>
My brother said he could solo there around 42th with his druid.  The MoBs are way underconned for their exp.  Quelar has gone from 30 to 34 and a half in the past 4 days.  However, he did have a little help.  A Beastlord friend went from low 45 to 47 and my brother's Druid went from mid 44 to almost 47.  Therefore I would not suggest someone in their low 30s going without some support.  At 46 some stuff is turning light blue to my brother's druid so they may only stick around for another two levels or so.  <br>
<br>
However, if I am there you are welcome and when you get to know the others I am sure you will be welcome even when I am not there.  Yesterday during the busy time there were 9 people in zone and we were 4 of them.  Until the word gets out this should be a great place to hunt.  <br>
<br>
Just FYI, you will HAVE to be OK with the guys of Katta Castellum.  I have seen some Ogres there so I am assuming most will start at least dubious.  <br>
<br>
For the people who need money, there are almost always high levels killing guards at the bank.  After a few kills they can't use the merchants or the bank anymore.  They just leave their corpses around and don't seem to mind others looting them.  Quelar looted corpses for about 20 minutes and got 180 plat.  If the guy hunting the guards is good then you can easily make 600 to 700 plat an hour just being a scavenger.  Just make sure you don't buff them while they attack the guards.  Quelar accidentally buffed one during a fight and got the faction hit when the guard died.  Now I am apprehensive in the city.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
